    <entry>
      <title>extends, casting, high order function</title>
      <link href="/hexo-blog/2023/04/02/extends/"/>
      <url>/hexo-blog/2023/04/02/extends/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>本节内容讲了：类与类的继承， Object类, 封装， 类型转换， 高阶函数 </p><p>详细内容:<a href="https://joshhug.gitbooks.io/hug61b/content/chap4/chap42.html">https://joshhug.gitbooks.io/hug61b/content/chap4/chap42.html</a></p><h2 id="继承"><a href="#继承" class="headerlink" title="继承"></a>继承</h2><div class="note warning flat"><p>构造器和私有成员不能被继承</p></div><p>继承和接口一样，关系为<code>is-a</code></p><h3 id="构造函数的继承"><a href="#构造函数的继承" class="headerlink" title="构造函数的继承"></a>构造函数的继承</h3><p>当子类创建无参构造函数，会隐式的继承父类的无参构造函数</p><figure class="highlight java"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">public</span> <span class="title function_">class_name</span><span class="params">()</span> &#123;</span><br><span class="line">  <span class="built_in">super</span>(); <span class="comment">//默认会进行继承,可以不添加</span></span><br><span class="line">  ...</span><br><span class="line">&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>当子类创建有参构造函数时，子类不会默认继承父类的有参构造函数，依旧是父类的无参构造函数<br>public class_name(int a) {<br>  super(a); //继承父类有参构造，必须显式调用<br>  …<br>}</p><p>总结：<br><div class="note warning flat"><p>子类只会默认继承无参构造函数</p></div></p><h2 id="Object"><a href="#Object" class="headerlink" title="Object"></a>Object</h2><p>所有声明的类都隐式的继承了Object类，换言之Object类是所有类(除自己)的父类，Object自身存在可以调用的方法，详情看<a href="https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/Object.html">这里</a></p><h2 id="封装"><a href="#封装" class="headerlink" title="封装"></a>封装</h2><p>编程中一个重要的技能就是降低程序的复杂度，越复杂的程序越难以理解和维护，一个好的程序员需要有降低复杂度的能力，那么如何降低复杂度呢？</p><h3 id="抽象"><a href="#抽象" class="headerlink" title="抽象"></a>抽象</h3><p>抽象是编程中一个重要的观念，想象你创建的程序是一个游戏机，你只知道它提供给你的按钮或接口，但不需要知道里面程序的逻辑是什么，电路是什么样的。</p><p>好的抽象总能提供当前抽象层次的内容，而不是跨越当前抽象层次，提供更底层的内容</p><h3 id="模块化"><a href="#模块化" class="headerlink" title="模块化"></a>模块化</h3><p>模块化是另一种降低复杂度的方法，通过类似搭积木的方式，将整个程序拆分成多个小部分。</p><p>模块化的任务：</p><p>不同模块之间彼此隐藏信息，就是说每个模块不需要知道对方的实现方式，通过提供接口的方式将不同模块结合起来</p><p>每个模块都互相独立，只实现自己的内容</p><p>不同模块能一同构建成满足需求的程序</p><h2 id="测试"><a href="#测试" class="headerlink" title="测试"></a>测试</h2><p>测试是面相用户的，因此程序内部实现了什么并不重要，关键在于程序使用时程序对用户的反馈是正确的。</p><h2 id="继承打破封装"><a href="#继承打破封装" class="headerlink" title="继承打破封装"></a>继承打破封装</h2><p>继承有时会给封装带来问题，即使封装内部实现十分完美</p><p>详情：<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EfxYiAN6YME">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EfxYiAN6YME</a></p><h2 id="编译类型和类型转换"><a href="#编译类型和类型转换" class="headerlink" title="编译类型和类型转换"></a>编译类型和类型转换</h2><p>编译器在处理声明对象时，会考虑对象的静态类型，如果对象有子类，则允许对象的动态类型为子类。</p><p>比如：狗类可以继承贵宾犬，但贵宾犬不能继承狗类</p><h3 id="类型转换"><a href="#类型转换" class="headerlink" title="类型转换"></a>类型转换</h3><p>如果对于两个不同子类的父类方法进行强制类型转换，就会造成以下后果</p><p>maxDog属于Dog类</p><figure class="highlight java"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="type">Poodle</span> <span class="variable">frank</span> <span class="operator">=</span> <span class="keyword">new</span> <span class="title class_">Poodle</span>(<span class="string">&quot;Frank&quot;</span>, <span class="number">5</span>);</span><br><span class="line"><span class="type">Malamute</span> <span class="variable">frankSr</span> <span class="operator">=</span> <span class="keyword">new</span> <span class="title class_">Malamute</span>(<span class="string">&quot;Frank Sr.&quot;</span>, <span class="number">100</span>);</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="type">Poodle</span> <span class="variable">largerPoodle</span> <span class="operator">=</span> (Poodle) maxDog(frank, frankSr); <span class="comment">// runtime exception!</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>因此类型转换具有一定风险，但在某些场合又很方便</p><h2 id="高阶函数"><a href="#高阶函数" class="headerlink" title="高阶函数"></a>高阶函数</h2><p>高阶函数简单来说就是在函数里以函数为参数</p><p>在python里是这样的：</p><figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title function_">tenX</span>(<span class="params">x</span>):</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="number">10</span>*x</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title function_">do_twice</span>(<span class="params">f, x</span>):</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">return</span> f(f(x))</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>在Java需要这样：</p><figure class="highlight java"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br><span class="line">15</span><br><span class="line">16</span><br><span class="line">17</span><br><span class="line">18</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">public</span> <span class="keyword">interface</span> <span class="title class_">IntUnaryFunction</span> &#123;</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="type">int</span> <span class="title function_">apply</span><span class="params">(<span class="type">int</span> x)</span>;</span><br><span class="line">&#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">public</span> <span class="keyword">class</span> <span class="title class_">TenX</span> <span class="keyword">implements</span> <span class="title class_">IntUnaryFunction</span> &#123;</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="comment">/* Returns ten times the argument. */</span></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">public</span> <span class="type">int</span> <span class="title function_">apply</span><span class="params">(<span class="type">int</span> x)</span> &#123;</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="number">10</span> * x;</span><br><span class="line">    &#125;</span><br><span class="line">&#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">public</span> <span class="keyword">static</span> <span class="type">int</span> <span class="title function_">do_twice</span><span class="params">(IntUnaryFunction f, <span class="type">int</span> x)</span> &#123;</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">return</span> f.apply(f.apply(x));</span><br><span class="line">&#125;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">//输出是这样的</span></span><br><span class="line">System.out.println(do_twice(<span class="keyword">new</span> <span class="title class_">TenX</span>(), <span class="number">2</span>));</span><br><span class="line"></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>可见，Java在函数式编程是非常弱的</p><h2 id="总结"><a href="#总结" class="headerlink" title="总结"></a>总结</h2><p>VengefulSLList extends SLList means VengefulSLList “is-an” SLList, and inherits all of SLList’s members:</p><ul><li>Variables, methods nested classes</li><li>Not constructors Subclass constructors must invoke superclass constructor first. The super keyword can be used to invoke overridden superclass methods and constructors.</li><li><p>Invocation of overridden methods follows two simple rules:</p></li><li><p>Compiler plays it safe and only allows us to do things according to the static type.</p></li><li>For overridden methods (not overloaded methods), the actual method invoked is based on the dynamic type of the invoking expression</li><li>Can use casting to overrule compiler type checking.</li></ul>]]></content>
      
      
